<h3 id="find">Find and manage users</h3>

<p>To locate a user or users:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Select a category on the user group tree.</li>
	<li>You can search (for) users by using one of the attributes displayed in the tab menu. Click an attribute to activate a search field:</li>
	<img src="image/doc/users/search1.bmp">
	<li>Enter search criteria and press "Enter".</li>
	<img src="image/doc/users/search2.bmp">
	<p>Results maching your criteria appears below.</p>
	<li>You can sort users ascending or descending by selecting "up" or "down" arrows next to appropriate attribute:</li>
	<img src="image/doc/users/sort.bmp">
	<li>You can also change attributes displayed in the toolbar:</li>
	<ol>
		<li>Click "Columns" on the right:</li>
		<img src="image/doc/users/columns.bmp"/>
		<li>Select or remove attributes by checking or clearing a checkbox next to appropriate attribute:</li>
		<img src="image/doc/users/select_attributes.bmp"/>
		<li>Click "Change Columns" to save changes.</li>
	</ol>
</ul>

<p>To edit a user or users:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Select users by marking a checkbox at the left.</li>
	<li>Click "With selected" drop-down list and choose an action to apply.</li>
	<li>To open user's details click the users' email.</li>
	<p>You can edit user's info and view his or her orders (...)</p>
</ul>

<h3 id="add">Add new user</h3>

<p>Users should be added to their appropriate user groups. To add a user:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Click a user group on the tree.</li>
	<li>Click the "Add new user" link.</li>
	<li>Complete the form to add the user:</li>
	<img src="image/doc/users/add.bmp"/>
	<li>Click the "Save" button.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="user_group">Add new user group</h3>

<p>To add a user group:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Click the "Add group" link (below the user group tree).</li>
	<li>Click on the "Group datails" tab to enter groups name and description if necessary.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="permissions">Setting administration permissions</h3>

<p>Except for customer, all the other users can have administations rights which can be set in the "Permissions" section.</p>

<ul>
	<li>Click a user group on the tree.</li>
	<li>Click on the "Permissions" tab.</li>
	<p>You can manage administration rights my checking necessary roles at their appropriate groups.</p>
	<li>Click "Save" when done.</li>
</ul>
